// @run
// @log 6
// USAGE-DRIVEN NULLABLE HOLE (A-infer-null), headline case: an un-annotated
// `let x = null` is NOT pinned to the exact `null` type — `null` is hole-bearing
// (it inhabits every `T | null`). A later `x = 5` fills the hole's `T`, so `x` is
// `i32 | null`. Flow-narrowing strips the `| null` on the straight line after the
// write, so `x + 1` carries no null tax (no spurious null check) and runs. This
// used to error `expected null, got 5` (the old exact-`null` pin).
let x = null
x = 5
print(x + 1)
